2-1. 로그 오즈비 구하기

word_sympathy <- word_noun %>%
  rename(like = like,
         dislike = dislike) %>%
  
  mutate(diff = like - dislike,
         sympathy = ifelse(diff >=  1, "like",
                           ifelse(diff <= -1, "dislike", "neutral")))

word_sympathy %>%
  distinct(id, .keep_all = T) %>%
  count(sympathy, sort = T)
## # A tibble: 3 × 2
##   sympathy     n
##   <chr>    <int>
## 1 like      1581
## 2 neutral    211
## 3 dislike    144
frequency_sympathy <- word_sympathy %>%
  count(sympathy, word) %>%             
  filter(str_count(word) > 1 &          
           sympathy != "centrism")        

library(tidyr)
frequency_wide <- frequency_sympathy %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = sympathy,
              values_from = n,
              values_fill = list(n = 0))

frequency_wide <- frequency_wide %>%
  mutate(log_odds_ratio = log(((like    + 1) / (sum(like    + 1))) /
                                ((dislike + 1) / (sum(dislike + 1)))))

frequency_wide %>%
  arrange(-log_odds_ratio)

## 
## 군사독재끝내니 검찰독재 로
find_word <- function(df, x, keyword, n = 6) {
  

  font <- combine_styles(make_style("ivory"),
                         make_style("deeppink", bg = TRUE),
                         make_style("bold"))
  

  df %>%
    filter(str_detect({{x}}, keyword)) %>%                  
    head(n) %>%                                             
    mutate(x = paste0("[", row_number(), "] ", {{x}}),     
           x = paste0(str_replace_all(x,
                                      keyword,
                                      font(keyword)))) %>%  
    pull(x) %>%                                             
    cat(sep = "\n\n")                                       
}

## [3] 군부독재의 실체

3-1. TF-IDF 구하기

# 단어 목록 생성
category1 <- "연기 | 배우 | 정우성 | 황정민"
category2 <- " 전두환 | 전두 | 정권 "
category3 <- "쿠데타 | 권력 | 군인 | 독재"

bind_category <- bind_rows(
  word_sympathy %>%
    filter(str_detect(reply, category1)) %>%
    mutate(category = "배우"),
  
  word_sympathy %>%
    filter(str_detect(reply, category2)) %>%
    mutate(category = "전두환"),
  
  word_sympathy %>%
    filter(str_detect(reply, category3)) %>%
    mutate(category = "쿠데타"))


# 카테고리별 빈도
bind_category %>%
  group_by(id) %>%
  distinct(category, .keep_all = T) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  count(category)
## # A tibble: 3 × 2
##   category     n
##   <chr>    <int>
## 1 배우       170
## 2 전두환      71
## 3 쿠데타      59
# 불용어 목록 생성
stopword_category <- c("연기" , "배우" , "정우성", "황정민",
                       "전두환", "전두", "정권",
                       "쿠데타", "권력", "군인", "독재")


# 카테고리별 단어 빈도 구하기
frequency_category <- bind_category %>%
  filter(!word %in% stopword_category) %>%  
  
  group_by(id) %>%                          
  distinct(word, .keep_all = T) %>%         
  ungroup() %>%                             
  
  count(category, word, sort = T) %>%       
  filter(str_count(word) >= 2)              


# tf-idf 구하기
tfidf_category <- frequency_category %>%
  bind_tf_idf(term = word,
              document = category,
              n = n) %>%
  arrange(-tf_idf)

tfidf_category

  separate_rows(word_pos, sep = "[+]") %>%                
  filter(str_detect(word_pos, "/n|/pv|/pa")) %>%            
  mutate(word = ifelse(str_detect(word_pos, "/pv|/pa"),     
                       str_replace(word_pos, "/.*$", "다"),  
                       str_remove(word_pos, "/.*$"))) %>%    
  filter(str_count(word) >= 2) %>%                          
  arrange(id)

graph_cors <- word_cors %>%

         group = as.factor(group_infomap()))    

library(ggraph)

  geom_node_point(aes(size = centrality,         
                      color = group),            
                  show.legend = F) +

4-2. 엔그램으로 연이어 사용된 단어 살펴보기

# 바이그램으로 토큰화
line_comment <- separate_pos_movie %>%
  group_by(id) %>%
  summarise(sentence = paste(word, collapse = " "))

bigram_comment <- line_comment %>%
  unnest_tokens(input = sentence,
                output = bigram,
                token = "ngrams",
                n = 2)

bigram_comment
## # A tibble: 17,799 × 2
##       id bigram         
##    <int> <chr>

## # ℹ 17,789 more rows
# 바이어그램의 단어쌍 빈도 구하기
bigram_seprated <- bigram_comment %>%
  separate(bigram, c("word1", "word2"), sep = " ")

pair_bigram <- bigram_seprated %>%
  count(word1, word2, sort = T) %>%
  na.omit()

# 명사 추출
noun_movie <- movie %>%
  distinct(reply, .keep_all = T) %>%                  
  filter(str_count(reply, boundary("word")) >= 3) %>% 
  unnest_tokens(input = reply,                        
                output = word,
                token = extractNoun,
                drop = F) %>%
  filter(str_count(word) > 1)

# 중복, 고빈도 단어 제거
unique_noun_movie <- noun_movie %>%
  group_by(id) %>%                                   
  distinct(word, .keep_all = T) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  add_count(word) %>%                                  
  filter(n <= 200) %>%
  select(id, word)
